androidx.test.orchestrator.listeners

Class OrchestrationXmlTestRunListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • androidx.test.orchestrator.listeners.OrchestrationRunListener
      • androidx.test.orchestrator.listeners.OrchestrationXmlTestRunListener

  • public class OrchestrationXmlTestRunListener
extends OrchestrationRunListener
    Writes JUnit results to an XML files in a format consistent with Ant's XMLJUnitResultFormatter.

    Creates a separate XML file per test run.

    This is a copy of com.android.ddmlib.testrunner.XmlTestRunListener made specificly for AndroidTestOrchestrator. Changes include:

    • makes code android-compatible.
    • extends OrchestrationRunListener instead of implementing the similar com.android.ddmlib.testrunner.ITestRunListener interface to easily attach it to AndroidTestOrchestrator.
    • writes XML to /sdcard/odo/ by default.
    • prints start-time and end-time of each test in XML.
    • fixes a few java coding style problems.
    See Also:
    https://svn.jenkins-ci.org/trunk/hudson/dtkit/dtkit-format/dtkit-junit-model/src/main/resources/com/thalesgroup/dtkit/junit/model/xsd/junit-4.xsd

Generated javadoc for the new package structure to make it clearer which packages are bundled with the Android operating system, and which are packaged with your app's APK. Going forward, the android.* package hierarchy will be reserved for Android packages that ship with the operating system; other packages will be issued in the new androidx.* package hiearchy.
